PROTOTYPE FEEDBACK
An online survey made with Google Forms was used to gather input in order to assess the SCHOLARITY prototype. Many participants, mostly students were given the survey link and asked to examine the prototype and share their thoughts about the system.

The survey included:
- Ease of navigation
- Usefulness of platform features
- System functionality
- User interface design
- Overall usefulness of the platform

A number of answers were gathered. The majority of participants said that navigating the website was simple or extremely simple. Most users said that the features of the system operated as intended.

According to participants, the platform's most beneficial features are:
- Learning Materials
- Download Resources
- Book Tutor Session

Additionally, the majority of respondents gave the overall user interface design high ratings mostly between 4 and 5 out of 5. For students searching for academic resources, the platform was helpful or extremely helpful by numerous users.
According to the feedback, the SCHOLARITY platform offers students a practical and easily accessible way to locate study materials, watch lectures, and get in touch with tutors.


USER TESTING NOTES
User testing of the SCHOLARITY prototype was conducted by asking participants to interact with the system and evaluate different parts of the interface through a structured Google Forms survey.
During the testing process, users were asked to perform actions such as browsing educational resources, viewing tutor profiles, and checking video lectures.
Some minor issues were observed during testing. A few users suggested improving the navigability of certain sections and making the interface slightly more visually engaging.
